At this point, my pieces and pawns are in such a mess, I'm hoping he'll trade the bishop for the knight and win back his pawn. Then the question is whose remaining minor piece is worse off. Back when I was up a pawn in this game, I was content to let the other game be a draw. But now, even though I'm materially up, he's ahead in just about every other aspect of the game.

I don't think he can break through. If I can get my rook over to d1, I'll feel ahead. He probably plays Re8 to threaten Nxf4 with my pawn pinned. So I'd have to go back to f2, and he can  move the rook back to d8 ... and a draw. But I won the other game in the match, and my teammate split his games, so all I need in this game is a draw for us to win the match.
